# RA2 Game Stability

The Red Alert 2 / Yuri's Revenge NAS golden master depends on pinning each live `gamemd.exe` process to exactly one assigned CPU.

- Do not remove or bypass `RA2_GAME_CPUSET`, `taskset -c "$GAME_CPUSET"`, or the watchdog re-pin of `gamemd.exe`.
- Player 1 should default to CPU `0`; player 2 should default to CPU `1`; future players should default to `PLAYER_ID - 1`.
- If crashes or lockups recur, debug Wine/runtime/process state instead of blocking normal gameplay inputs.
- Keep the golden-master details in `docs/GOLDEN_MASTER.md` current whenever the stable runtime changes.
